venue.name: Faculté des Sciences et Techniques de Tanger
venue.address_1: Ancienne Route de l’Aéroport, Km 10, Ziaten Boukhalef

events.description:
What’s GDG :

Google Developer Groups (GDGs) are for developers who are interested in Google's developer technology; everything from the Android, Chrome, Drive, and Google Cloud platforms, to product APIs like the Cast API, Maps API, and YouTube API.

A GDG can take many forms -- from just a few people getting together to watch our latest video, to large gatherings with demos and tech talks, to events like code sprints and hackathons. However, at the core, GDGs are focused on developers and technical content, and the core audience should be developers.

Program :

10:00 Welcoming & Greeting

11:00 What is GDG by @gdgtangier

11:30 How to Learn the Right Way by @souhailmerroun

12:00 Women Techmakers by @benkhadrajihane, @zerhajar

12:30 Live stream with @laurencemoroney

13:00 Break & networking

Register :

To save your seat, please register here: https://goo.gl/forms/PWsKgieKMKEGCwcR2

events.name: Cloud Study Jams
events.description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin?
Join us for our Cloud Study Jam! Together we'll work through three Google Cloud Platform Essentials labs, then you will get free access to the next quest so you can finish this series of labs at home to get a Google-hosted badge for your online profile. You will be able to get hands-on experience with Docker, Kubernetes and Scientific Data Processing, which will earn you additional badges.
Join this meetup to get official Google training, a $70+ value, free of charge.
Bring a laptop (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed.

Agenda:
4:00pm: Welcoming and presentation.
4:30pm: Three Google Cloud Platform Essentials labs.
6:00pm: Break.
6:30pm: Intro to Docker or Scientific Data Processing lab.
7:30pm: Event ends.

• What to bring
laptop with the charger.

events.name: Machine Learning Study Jam
events.description:

This course is intended for those who wish to learn about ML from a practical, applied perspective that will enable you to use machine learning in your everyday projects and learn about the power of TensorFlow. events.name: DevFest OnAir Tangier - watching party
events.description:
We are organizing a watching party of the first Devfest OnAir in Tangier!

DevFest OnAir is an online conference featuring sessions from DevFest events around the globe. These community-led developer sessions are hosted by GDG (Google Developer Groups) focused on community, networking and learning about Google technologies. With over 500 communities and DevFest events happening all over the world, DevFest OnAir brings this global experience online for the first time!
Exclusive content.
DevFest OnAir includes exclusive content from Google. Switch between three separate tracks: Cloud; Mobile; Voice, Web & more. Sessions cover multiple products such as Android, Google Cloud Platform, Firebase, Google Assistant, Flutter, machine learning with TensorFlow, and mobile web.

Tailored to your time zone.
Anyone can join, no matter where you are. We’re hosting three broadcasts around the world, around the clock, so there’s a convenient time for you to join no matter where you are at home or at work.

Ask us a question live.
Our live Q&A forum will be open throughout the online event to spark conversation and get you the answers you need.

Fun!
Join the fun with interactive trivia during DevFest OnAir where you can receive something special! Every participant will receive one free month of learning on Qwiklabs.

Location: https://goo.gl/maps/mAztyFkpDiz

Schedule
CLOUD track of EMEA Pre Show, Behind the Scenes in Nantes.
https://devfest.withgoogle.com/events/devfestonair18/schedule?talk=preshow-emea

events.name: Google Cloud StudyJams
events.description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam!

Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console, Kubernetes, Security, IoT on Cloud, and Machine Learning.

Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete with any labs you want

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

Agenda:

1:00pm: Opening & Check-in
2:00pm: presentation and Introduction
4:00pm: GCP Essentials labs, first lab about Introduction to Docker
6:00pm: Second lab about Introduction to Kubernetes
6:30pm: Event ends

Time zone: GMT+1

Can't wait to see you all!

events.name: Machine Learning: Real-world applications
events.description:
Machine Learning: Real-World Applications

What is Machine Learning ? and What are some interesting real-world applications of Machine Learning?
In this Meetup, we are going to answer these two questions! which will give a good starting point for people who want to solve new and interesting problems in the real world. We will help you understand "What Machine Learning is all about" and guide you through the process of building and using Machine Learning Models.

In this Meetup, Abdelhamid EL HASSANI will cover the following topics in a 120 min short presentation:

AN OVERVIEW OF MACHINE LEARNING
-> What is machine learning?

REAL-WORLD APPLICATIONS OF MACHINE LEARNING
-> Image & Speech Recognition
-> Medical Diagnosis
-> Prediction
-> Classification
